derivation: or (shortened) אֶלְיוֹעֵינַי; from H413 (אֵל) and H3068 (יְהֹוָה) and H5869 (עַיִן); towards Jehovah (are) my eyes;
outline:
Elioenai or Elihoenai = "unto Jehovah are my eyes"
  1. a Korahite temple doorkeeper, son of Meshelemiah
  2. two men with foreign wife during the exile; one a priest
  3. a son of Neariah
  4. a Simeonite
  5. a Benjamite, son of Becher
strongs_def: Eljehoenai or Eljoenai, the name of seven Israelites
